# Widget Sizing System (1x, 2x, 3x Width)

**Created:** November 16, 2025
**Status:** 🟡 PLANNING
**Priority:** P2 - HIGH (User-requested feature)

---

## Overview

Implement widget sizing system that allows users to set individual widgets to 1x, 2x, or 3x width on the dashboard. This uses React Masonry CSS's built-in column spanning capability to create a flexible, responsive dashboard layout.

---

## Problem Statement

**Current Behavior:**
- All dashboard widgets are the same width (single column in masonry layout)
- Users cannot emphasize important widgets or create visual hierarchy
- Large data widgets (Calendar, Kanban) constrained to single column

**Desired Behavior:**
- Each widget can be set to 1x, 2x, or 3x width
- Width preference persists per widget ID
- Responsive: 3x becomes 2x on tablet, 1x on mobile
- Smooth transitions when changing sizes
- Settings accessible via widget menu (gear icon)

**User Value:**
- Visual hierarchy (highlight important widgets)
- Better use of screen space (Calendar/Kanban at 2x-3x width)
- Personalized dashboard layout
- Professional appearance

